---
import PortalLayout from "../layouts/PortalLayout.astro";
---

<PortalLayout title="Developers" mainBg="#ecfdf5">
  <div class="max-w-4xl">
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-2">Developers</h1>
    <p class="text-stone-600 mb-8">Technical reference for the SMP dev team.</p>

    <div class="space-y-8">
      <!-- Naming Conventions -->
      <section class="bg-white border border-stone-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-red-700 mb-4">Naming Conventions</h2>
        <p class="text-stone-700 mb-3">To avoid confusion, the team uses these terms consistently:</p>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-stone-700">
          <li><code class="bg-stone-100 px-2 py-1 rounded text-xs font-bold">bethel</code> = the server (Hetzner VPS at 100.114.220.65)</li>
          <li><code class="bg-stone-100 px-2 py-1 rounded text-xs font-bold">dev</code> = always the git branch (where all work happens)</li>
          <li><code class="bg-stone-100 px-2 py-1 rounded text-xs font-bold">main</code> = always the production branch (triggers Netlify build)</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="text-stone-500 text-sm mt-3">Example: "SSH into Bethel, push to dev, Kevin approves merge to main."</p>
      </section>

      <!-- SSH Access -->
      <section class="bg-white border border-stone-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-red-700 mb-4">SSH Access to Bethel</h2>
        <p class="text-stone-600 mb-4">Connect to the development server via Tailscale:</p>
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between bg-stone-100 px-4 py-3 rounded font-mono text-sm text-stone-700 overflow-x-auto">
          <span>ssh bethel</span>
        </div>
        <p class="text-stone-500 text-sm mt-3">Requires Tailscale VPN. SSH config alias is set up in <code class="bg-stone-100 px-1 rounded text-xs">~/.ssh/config</code> pointing to <code class="bg-stone-100 px-1 rounded text-xs">100.114.220.65</code>. See <a href="/connecting" class="text-red-700 hover:underline">Connecting</a> for Tailscale setup.</p>
      </section>

      <!-- Bethel User Accounts -->
      <section class="bg-white border border-stone-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-red-700 mb-4">Bethel User Accounts</h2>
        <p class="text-stone-600 mb-4">Each developer has their own SSH account. Passwords are in the <strong>Bethel Admin Guide</strong> &mdash; ask Kevin for access.</p>
        <div class="overflow-x-auto">
          <table class="w-full text-sm">
            <thead>
              <tr class="border-b border-stone-200">
                <th class="text-left py-2 pr-4 text-stone-500 font-semibold">Name</th>
                <th class="text-left py-2 pr-4 text-stone-500 font-semibold">Username</th>
                <th class="text-left py-2 pr-4 text-stone-500 font-semibold">Role</th>
                <th class="text-left py-2 text-stone-500 font-semibold">Preview Ports</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody class="text-stone-700">
              <tr class="border-b border-stone-100"><td class="py-2 pr-4">Kevin White</td><td class="py-2 pr-4 font-mono text-xs">kevin</td><td class="py-2 pr-4">Owner</td><td class="py-2 font-mono text-xs">4321&ndash;4340</td></tr>
              <tr class="border-b border-stone-100"><td class="py-2 pr-4">Nathan Bost</td><td class="py-2 pr-4 font-mono text-xs">nathan</td><td class="py-2 pr-4">Technical / Git</td><td class="py-2 font-mono text-xs">4341&ndash;4360</td></tr>
              <tr class="border-b border-stone-100"><td class="py-2 pr-4">Jufrey</td><td class="py-2 pr-4 font-mono text-xs">jufrey</td><td class="py-2 pr-4">Web Developer</td><td class="py-2 font-mono text-xs">4361&ndash;4380</td></tr>
              <tr class="border-b border-stone-100"><td class="py-2 pr-4">Justin Keishing</td><td class="py-2 pr-4 font-mono text-xs">justin</td><td class="py-2 pr-4">Artist (Arts by Justin)</td><td class="py-2 font-mono text-xs">4381&ndash;4400</td></tr>
              <tr class="border-b border-stone-100"><td class="py-2 pr-4">Vinit</td><td class="py-2 pr-4 font-mono text-xs">vinit</td><td class="py-2 pr-4">Developer</td><td class="py-2 font-mono text-xs">4401&ndash;4420</td></tr>
              <tr class="border-b border-stone-100"><td class="py-2 pr-4">GHL Support</td><td class="py-2 pr-4 font-mono text-xs">support</td><td class="py-2 pr-4">GHL / CRM</td><td class="py-2 font-mono text-xs">&mdash;</td></tr>
              <tr><td class="py-2 pr-4">Deploy</td><td class="py-2 pr-4 font-mono text-xs">deploy</td><td class="py-2 pr-4">Shared service account — secrets, config, all repos</td><td class="py-2 font-mono text-xs">&mdash;</td></tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>
        <p class="text-stone-500 text-xs mt-3">Preview ports prevent conflicts when multiple developers run dev servers simultaneously.</p>
        <p class="text-stone-500 text-xs mt-1"><strong>Request routing:</strong> All requests (content, design, builds, deploys, client work) route through Kevin White.</p>

        <h3 class="font-bold text-stone-800 mt-6 mb-3">Per-Site Port Allocation</h3>
        <p class="text-stone-600 text-sm mb-3">Each site has a dedicated dev server port on Bethel:</p>
        <div class="overflow-x-auto">
          <table class="w-full text-sm">
            <thead>
              <tr class="border-b border-stone-200">
                <th class="text-left py-2 pr-4 text-stone-500 font-semibold">Site</th>
                <th class="text-left py-2 text-stone-500 font-semibold">Port</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody class="text-stone-700">
              <tr class="border-b border-stone-100"><td class="py-2 pr-4">SMP</td><td class="py-2 font-mono text-xs">4321</td></tr>
              <tr class="border-b border-stone-100"><td class="py-2 pr-4">artsbyjustin</td><td class="py-2 font-mono text-xs">4322</td></tr>
              <tr class="border-b border-stone-100"><td class="py-2 pr-4">FHB</td><td class="py-2 font-mono text-xs">4323</td></tr>
              <tr class="border-b border-stone-100"><td class="py-2 pr-4">WOY</td><td class="py-2 font-mono text-xs">4324</td></tr>
              <tr class="border-b border-stone-100"><td class="py-2 pr-4">The Kohler Group</td><td class="py-2 font-mono text-xs">4325</td></tr>
              <tr class="border-b border-stone-100"><td class="py-2 pr-4">Portal</td><td class="py-2 font-mono text-xs">4326</td></tr>
              <tr class="border-b border-stone-100"><td class="py-2 pr-4">Tools API</td><td class="py-2 font-mono text-xs">4327 <span class="text-stone-400">(reserved)</span></td></tr>
              <tr class="border-b border-stone-100"><td class="py-2 pr-4">clowning-from-the-heart</td><td class="py-2 font-mono text-xs">4328</td></tr>
              <tr class="border-b border-stone-100"><td class="py-2 pr-4">scripture-alive</td><td class="py-2 font-mono text-xs">4329</td></tr>
              <tr class="border-b border-stone-100"><td class="py-2 pr-4">10-billion-travelers</td><td class="py-2 font-mono text-xs">4330</td></tr>
              <tr><td class="py-2 pr-4">john-watts-agency</td><td class="py-2 font-mono text-xs">4331</td></tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Managing Users -->
      <section class="bg-white border border-stone-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-red-700 mb-4">Managing Bethel Accounts</h2>
        <p class="text-stone-600 mb-4">Claude handles all user management on Bethel. No manual commands needed.</p>
        <div class="space-y-4">
          <div class="p-3 bg-stone-50 rounded-lg">
            <p class="text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-stone-400 mb-1">Add a user</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-stone-700 italic">"Create a new Bethel account for [Full Name]. Their email is [email]. Their role is [role]."</p>
          </div>
          <div class="p-3 bg-stone-50 rounded-lg">
            <p class="text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-stone-400 mb-1">Remove a user</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-stone-700 italic">"Remove [username]'s Bethel account."</p>
          </div>
          <div class="p-3 bg-stone-50 rounded-lg">
            <p class="text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-stone-400 mb-1">Reset a password</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-stone-700 italic">"Reset the password for [username]."</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- MCP Servers -->
      <section class="bg-white border border-stone-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-red-700 mb-4">MCP Servers</h2>
        <p class="text-stone-600 mb-4">Every site directory on Bethel has a <code class="bg-stone-100 px-2 py-1 rounded text-xs">.mcp.json</code> symlinked from <code class="bg-stone-100 px-2 py-1 rounded text-xs">/home/deploy/.mcp.json</code>. This gives Claude Code access to all MCP integrations automatically. The config is gitignored (contains API keys).</p>
        <div class="overflow-x-auto">
          <table class="w-full text-sm">
            <thead>
              <tr class="border-b border-stone-200">
                <th class="text-left py-2 pr-4 text-stone-500 font-semibold">Server</th>
                <th class="text-left py-2 pr-4 text-stone-500 font-semibold">Service</th>
                <th class="text-left py-2 text-stone-500 font-semibold">Purpose</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody class="text-stone-700">
              <tr class="border-b border-stone-100"><td class="py-2 pr-4 font-semibold">Stitch</td><td class="py-2 pr-4">Google Stitch 2.0</td><td class="py-2">AI design — generates page designs and design systems (Gemini 3.1 Pro)</td></tr>
              <tr class="border-b border-stone-100"><td class="py-2 pr-4 font-semibold">Sanity</td><td class="py-2 pr-4">mcp.sanity.io</td><td class="py-2">Content management and image assets</td></tr>
              <tr class="border-b border-stone-100"><td class="py-2 pr-4 font-semibold">Netlify</td><td class="py-2 pr-4">@netlify/mcp</td><td class="py-2">Hosting, deploys, build status</td></tr>
              <tr class="border-b border-stone-100"><td class="py-2 pr-4 font-semibold">Cloudflare</td><td class="py-2 pr-4">@cloudflare/mcp-server-cloudflare</td><td class="py-2">DNS, SSL, CDN, R2 storage</td></tr>
              <tr class="border-b border-stone-100"><td class="py-2 pr-4 font-semibold">Playwright</td><td class="py-2 pr-4">@anthropic/mcp-playwright</td><td class="py-2">Browser screenshots and testing</td></tr>
              <tr class="border-b border-stone-100"><td class="py-2 pr-4 font-semibold">GHL</td><td class="py-2 pr-4">services.leadconnectorhq.com</td><td class="py-2">CRM, forms, contacts, marketing automation</td></tr>
              <tr><td class="py-2 pr-4 font-semibold">Google Docs</td><td class="py-2 pr-4">@a-bonus/google-docs-mcp</td><td class="py-2">Team documents and content drafts</td></tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>
        <p class="text-stone-500 text-xs mt-3">Stitch is the standard SMP workflow for all new site builds and major redesigns. See the <a href="/playbook" class="text-red-700 hover:underline">Playbook</a> for the full 4-step design workflow.</p>
      </section>

      <!-- Security -->
      <section class="bg-white border border-stone-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-red-700 mb-4">Security Notes</h2>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-stone-700 text-sm">
          <li>&bull; Never commit passwords or API keys to Git</li>
          <li>&bull; All secrets are stored in <code class="bg-stone-100 px-1 rounded text-xs">~/.secrets</code> on each account (chmod 600)</li>
          <li>&bull; The <code class="bg-stone-100 px-1 rounded text-xs">deploy</code> account holds all shared secrets — work happens here but personal Claude sessions stay in your own account</li>
          <li>&bull; Claude Team uses OAuth (no API key) — authenticated via Kevin's Claude Team subscription</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <!-- Session Tips -->
      <section class="bg-white border border-stone-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-red-700 mb-4">Session Best Practices</h2>
        <p class="text-stone-600 mb-4">At the end of every session, tell Claude:</p>
        <div class="bg-stone-100 rounded px-4 py-3 text-sm italic text-stone-700 mb-4">"Update CLAUDE.md with what we did today"</div>
        <p class="text-stone-600 mb-4">At the start of a new session, tell Claude:</p>
        <div class="bg-stone-100 rounded px-4 py-3 text-sm italic text-stone-700">"Read CLAUDE.md — that's our current state. Then [your task]."</div>
        <p class="text-stone-500 text-xs mt-3">This gives every new session full context of what happened before.</p>
      </section>

      <!-- GitHub SSH Key Setup -->
      <section class="bg-white border border-stone-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-red-700 mb-4">GitHub SSH Key Setup</h2>
        <p class="text-stone-600 mb-4">Generate an SSH key and add it to your GitHub account so you can push/pull without entering passwords.</p>
        <div class="space-y-4">
          <div>
            <p class="text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-stone-400 mb-1">Step 1 — Generate a key</p>
            <div class="flex items-center justify-between bg-stone-100 px-4 py-3 rounded font-mono text-sm text-stone-700 overflow-x-auto">
              <span>ssh-keygen -t ed25519 -C "your@email.com"</span>
              <button class="copy-btn px-3 py-1 bg-red-50 hover:bg-red-100 text-red-700 rounded text-xs font-semibold ml-4 font-sans" data-copy='ssh-keygen -t ed25519 -C "your@email.com"'>Copy</button>
            </div>
            <p class="text-stone-500 text-xs mt-1">Press Enter to accept the default file location. Add a passphrase if desired.</p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <p class="text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-stone-400 mb-1">Step 2 — Copy the public key</p>
            <div class="flex items-center justify-between bg-stone-100 px-4 py-3 rounded font-mono text-sm text-stone-700 overflow-x-auto">
              <span>cat ~/.ssh/id_ed25519.pub</span>
              <button class="copy-btn px-3 py-1 bg-red-50 hover:bg-red-100 text-red-700 rounded text-xs font-semibold ml-4 font-sans" data-copy="cat ~/.ssh/id_ed25519.pub">Copy</button>
            </div>
            <p class="text-stone-500 text-xs mt-1">Copy the entire output (starts with <code class="bg-stone-100 px-1 rounded">ssh-ed25519</code>).</p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <p class="text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-stone-400 mb-1">Step 3 — Add to GitHub</p>
            <p class="text-stone-600 text-sm">Go to <a href="https://github.com/settings/keys" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-red-700 hover:underline">github.com/settings/keys</a> → <strong>New SSH key</strong> → paste the public key → Save.</p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <p class="text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-stone-400 mb-1">Step 4 — Test the connection</p>
            <div class="flex items-center justify-between bg-stone-100 px-4 py-3 rounded font-mono text-sm text-stone-700 overflow-x-auto">
              <span>ssh -T git@github.com</span>
              <button class="copy-btn px-3 py-1 bg-red-50 hover:bg-red-100 text-red-700 rounded text-xs font-semibold ml-4 font-sans" data-copy="ssh -T git@github.com">Copy</button>
            </div>
            <p class="text-stone-500 text-xs mt-1">You should see: "Hi [username]! You've successfully authenticated."</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Code Server -->
      <section class="bg-white border border-stone-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-red-700 mb-4">Code Server (VS Code in Browser)</h2>
        <p class="text-stone-600 mb-4">Browser-based IDE with full project access:</p>
        <a
          href="https://dev.spiritmediapublishing.com"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener noreferrer"
          class="inline-block px-4 py-2 bg-red-50 border border-stone-200 hover:bg-white hover:border-red-700 text-red-700 text-sm font-semibold rounded transition-colors"
        >
          Open Code Server
        </a>
        <p class="text-stone-500 text-sm mt-3">Requires Tailscale VPN access</p>
      </section>

      <!-- GitHub Organization -->
      <section class="bg-white border border-stone-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-red-700 mb-4">GitHub Organization</h2>
        <p class="text-stone-600 mb-4">
          <a href="https://github.com/Spirit-Media-US" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-red-700 hover:underline">
            Spirit-Media-US
          </a>
        </p>
        <div class="space-y-2">
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-stone-700">Repositories:</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-1 text-stone-600">
            <li>• <code class="bg-stone-100 px-2 py-1 rounded text-xs">spirit-media-publishing</code></li>
            <li>• <code class="bg-stone-100 px-2 py-1 rounded text-xs">FHB</code> (Father's Heart Bible)</li>
            <li>• <code class="bg-stone-100 px-2 py-1 rounded text-xs">WOY</code> (Work On Yourself)</li>
            <li>• <code class="bg-stone-100 px-2 py-1 rounded text-xs">the-kohler-group</code></li>
            <li>• <code class="bg-stone-100 px-2 py-1 rounded text-xs">artsbyjustin</code></li>
            <li>• <code class="bg-stone-100 px-2 py-1 rounded text-xs">clowning-from-the-heart</code></li>
            <li>• <code class="bg-stone-100 px-2 py-1 rounded text-xs">scripture-alive</code></li>
            <li>• <code class="bg-stone-100 px-2 py-1 rounded text-xs">10-billion-travelers</code></li>
            <li>• <code class="bg-stone-100 px-2 py-1 rounded text-xs">john-watts-agency</code></li>
            <li>• <code class="bg-stone-100 px-2 py-1 rounded text-xs">tools-api</code> (pipeline server — private)</li>
            <li>• <code class="bg-stone-100 px-2 py-1 rounded text-xs">spirit-media-portal</code> (this site)</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Google Analytics -->
      <section class="bg-white border border-stone-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-red-700 mb-4">Google Analytics</h2>
        <p class="text-stone-600 mb-4">Access via <code class="bg-stone-100 px-2 py-1 rounded text-xs">admin@spiritmedia.us</code></p>
        <div class="space-y-2">
          <div class="flex items-center justify-between bg-stone-100 px-4 py-2 rounded">
            <div>
              <p class="text-stone-700 font-semibold">Google Tag Manager ID</p>
              <code class="text-xs text-stone-500">526725965</code>
            </div>
            <button class="copy-btn px-3 py-1 bg-red-50 hover:bg-opacity-30 text-red-700 rounded text-xs font-600" data-copy="526725965">
              Copy
            </button>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-center justify-between bg-stone-100 px-4 py-2 rounded">
            <div>
              <p class="text-stone-700 font-semibold">GA4 Property ID</p>
              <code class="text-xs text-stone-500">G-W3R21TNHTX</code>
            </div>
            <button class="copy-btn px-3 py-1 bg-red-50 hover:bg-opacity-30 text-red-700 rounded text-xs font-600" data-copy="G-W3R21TNHTX">
              Copy
            </button>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Credentials -->
      <section class="bg-white border border-stone-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-red-700 mb-4">Credentials & Secrets</h2>
        <p class="text-stone-600 mb-2">All sensitive credentials are stored in:</p>
        <div class="bg-stone-100 px-4 py-2 rounded font-mono text-sm text-stone-700 mb-4">
          Bitwarden Vault
        </div>
        <p class="text-stone-500 text-sm">
          Ask a team lead for access. Never commit tokens or secrets to Git.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- Deploy Workflow -->
      <section class="bg-white border border-stone-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-red-700 mb-2">Deploy Workflow</h2>
        <p class="text-stone-600 text-sm">See the full deployment workflow, troubleshooting guide, and best practices on the <a href="/playbook" class="text-red-700 hover:underline font-semibold">Playbook</a>.</p>
      </section>

      <!-- Quick Start -->
      <section class="bg-white border border-stone-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-red-700 mb-4">Quick Start Checklist</h2>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-stone-700">
          <li>✓ Get your Bethel username from Kevin</li>
          <li>✓ Set up <a href="/connecting" class="text-red-700 hover:underline">Tailscale VPN</a> (see Connecting page)</li>
          <li>✓ SSH into Bethel: <code class="bg-stone-100 px-2 py-1 rounded text-xs">ssh bethel</code></li>
          <li>✓ Set up your <a href="https://github.com/settings/keys" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-red-700 hover:underline">GitHub SSH key</a> (see setup above)</li>
          <li>✓ Clone repos from Spirit-Media-US org</li>
          <li>✓ Install dependencies: <code class="bg-stone-100 px-2 py-1 rounded text-xs">npm install</code></li>
          <li>✓ Read the <a href="/playbook" class="text-red-700 hover:underline">Playbook</a> for deployment workflow</li>
          <li>✓ Read the <a href="/connecting" class="text-red-700 hover:underline">Connecting</a> page for Claude setup</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <!-- Shared Templates -->
      <section class="bg-white border border-stone-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-red-700 mb-4">Shared Templates</h2>
        <p class="text-stone-600 mb-4">Reusable checklists and scripts stored on Bethel. Tell Claude which template to run and it handles the rest.</p>

        <h3 class="font-bold text-stone-800 mb-2">Location</h3>
        <div class="bg-stone-100 px-4 py-3 rounded font-mono text-sm text-stone-700 mb-4">
          /home/deploy/bin/templates/
        </div>

        <h3 class="font-bold text-stone-800 mb-2">Available Templates</h3>
        <div class="overflow-x-auto mb-4">
          <table class="w-full text-sm text-left">
            <thead class="text-xs text-stone-500 uppercase border-b">
              <tr><th class="py-2 pr-4">Template</th><th class="py-2 pr-4">File</th><th class="py-2">Purpose</th></tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody class="text-stone-700">
              <tr class="border-b border-stone-100">
                <td class="py-2 pr-4 font-medium">Post-Launch Checklist</td>
                <td class="py-2 pr-4 font-mono text-xs">post-launch-checklist.md</td>
                <td class="py-2">58-item QA, SEO, accessibility, performance, and deployment checklist</td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>

        <h3 class="font-bold text-stone-800 mb-2">How to Use a Template</h3>
        <p class="text-stone-600 text-sm mb-2">Just tell Claude in plain English:</p>
        <div class="bg-stone-100 px-4 py-3 rounded font-mono text-sm text-stone-700 mb-2 italic">
          Run the post-launch checklist for thekohlergroup.net. Save the report and upload to Google Drive.
        </div>
        <p class="text-stone-500 text-xs mb-4">Claude reads the template, fills in the site details automatically from CLAUDE.md and the codebase, runs the audit, and uploads the report.</p>

        <h3 class="font-bold text-stone-800 mb-2">How to Add a New Template</h3>
        <p class="text-stone-600 text-sm mb-2">Build it with Claude on Bethel, then save:</p>
        <div class="bg-stone-100 px-4 py-3 rounded font-mono text-sm text-stone-700 mb-2">
          Save this template to /home/deploy/bin/templates/[template-name].md
        </div>
        <ul class="text-stone-600 text-sm space-y-1 ml-4 list-disc">
          <li>Use <code class="bg-stone-100 px-1 py-0.5 rounded text-xs">[PLACEHOLDERS]</code> for site-specific values</li>
          <li>Add a header: who created it, last updated, what it's for</li>
          <li>Requires deploy group membership (ask Kevin)</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <!-- New Rules (March 2026) -->
      <section class="bg-white border border-stone-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-red-700 mb-4">New Rules <span class="text-sm font-normal text-stone-500">(March 2026)</span></h2>
        <p class="text-stone-600 mb-4">Mandatory rules established 2026-03-30. These apply to all sessions and all developers.</p>
        <div class="space-y-4">
          <div class="p-3 bg-stone-50 rounded-lg">
            <p class="font-semibold text-stone-800 text-sm mb-1">Mandatory startup</p>
            <p class="text-stone-600 text-sm">Always <code class="bg-stone-100 px-2 py-1 rounded text-xs">cd ~/Sites/(slug) && claude</code> before working on any site. Running Claude from <code class="bg-stone-100 px-1 rounded text-xs">~/</code> or <code class="bg-stone-100 px-1 rounded text-xs">~/Sites/</code> is blocked.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="p-3 bg-stone-50 rounded-lg">
            <p class="font-semibold text-stone-800 text-sm mb-1">Pre-edit hook</p>
            <p class="text-stone-600 text-sm">A hook in <code class="bg-stone-100 px-1 rounded text-xs">settings.json</code> blocks edits to site files when CWD is <code class="bg-stone-100 px-1 rounded text-xs">~/</code> or <code class="bg-stone-100 px-1 rounded text-xs">~/Sites/</code>. This prevents bypassing per-project CLAUDE.md rules.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="p-3 bg-stone-50 rounded-lg">
            <p class="font-semibold text-stone-800 text-sm mb-1">Session hook</p>
            <p class="text-stone-600 text-sm">Warns when a site directory is not listed in the global CLAUDE.md.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="p-3 bg-stone-50 rounded-lg">
            <p class="font-semibold text-stone-800 text-sm mb-1">New site auto-detection</p>
            <p class="text-stone-600 text-sm">A cron job runs at 4 AM UTC, scans <code class="bg-stone-100 px-1 rounded text-xs">~/Sites/</code>, and auto-adds new repos to the global CLAUDE.md.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="p-3 bg-stone-50 rounded-lg">
            <p class="font-semibold text-stone-800 text-sm mb-1">MailtoLink required</p>
            <p class="text-stone-600 text-sm">Every site must have a <code class="bg-stone-100 px-1 rounded text-xs">MailtoLink</code> component. Bare <code class="bg-stone-100 px-1 rounded text-xs">mailto:</code> links are banned.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="p-3 bg-stone-50 rounded-lg">
            <p class="font-semibold text-stone-800 text-sm mb-1">CSP required</p>
            <p class="text-stone-600 text-sm">Every site must have a <code class="bg-stone-100 px-1 rounded text-xs">netlify.toml</code> with <code class="bg-stone-100 px-1 rounded text-xs">[[headers]]</code> including <code class="bg-stone-100 px-1 rounded text-xs">Content-Security-Policy</code>.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="p-3 bg-stone-50 rounded-lg">
            <p class="font-semibold text-stone-800 text-sm mb-1">Sanity tokens are project-scoped</p>
            <p class="text-stone-600 text-sm">Each Sanity project needs its own write token in <code class="bg-stone-100 px-1 rounded text-xs">.secrets</code>. Do not share tokens across projects.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Support -->
      <section class="bg-white border border-stone-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-red-700 mb-4">Need Help?</h2>
        <p class="text-stone-600">
          Check the <a href="/playbook" class="text-red-700 hover:underline">Playbook</a> for architecture & workflows, or direct questions to the team lead.
        </p>
      </section>
    </div>
  </div>

  <script>
    document.querySelectorAll('.copy-btn').forEach((btn) => {
      btn.addEventListener('click', function () {
        const text = this.getAttribute('data-copy');
        navigator.clipboard.writeText(text).then(() => {
          const originalText = this.textContent;
          this.textContent = 'Copied!';
          setTimeout(() => {
            this.textContent = originalText;
          }, 2000);
        });
      });
    });
  </script>
</PortalLayout>
